   Research and development expenses for fiscal 2018 increased
   $10.3 million, or 79.1%, compared to fiscal 2017. This increase was due
   primarily to increases of $3.9 million in product development and
   research costs, $3.3 million in personnel-related expenses, excluding
   stock-based compensation expense, resulting from increased headcount,
   and $1.1 million in web hosting fees to create new, as well as improve
   existing products and interactive software features on our platform.


